  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0dad\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dba\u0d9a\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc1\u0dda\u0dc2 \u0d89\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd3\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A special request from the speaker",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Speaker Mahinda Yapa Abeywardena said in a special statement at the opening of the Parliament that as the country as well as the whole world is watching the process happening in the Sri Lankan Parliament today, all MPs are requested to behave in an exemplary manner.",
        "It must be said that today is a historic day to elect the eighth executive president. On this special occasion, not only all of us as members of parliament, but the whole country and the whole world are undoubtedly paying more attention than usual to what is happening in the parliament today.",
        "At this time, I have stated that two officials will be on both sides to avoid bringing any mobile phone to the polling station, or to hand over the mobile phone if it is in his hand.",
        "It must be said that revealing one's vote or ballot paper or taking photos using a mobile phone is also against the pledge given to us according to the constitution of the government."
      ],
